===Etymology===
'''[[green]]''' + '''[[land]]''' (The origin of the "green" in "Greenland" is disputed; [[Icelandic]] [[saga]] says that the island was so named by [[w:Eric the Red|Eric the Red]] to make the island sound more pleasant than it was in order to lure potential settlers away from Iceland, or that it was much greener in his day; it is also said that his family came from [[Grønland]] in [[Norway]], and that he had traveled from a poor, black-stoned field in his homeland to large green meadows in Greenland)

===Proper noun===
'''Greenland'''

# A self-governing island that is a territory of [[Denmark]].

